# Conclave Cursor Rules

You are working in the **Conclave** repository. Conclave is a multi-agent orchestration framework.

## Architecture Knowledge (Hybrid: Global Runtime + Per-Project Context)

Conclave runs in **hybrid mode**. One global runtime serves any project directory; each project keeps its own memory and squads.

### Global (shared, user-wide)
- **Skill entry point**: `~/.claude/skills/conclave/SKILL.md` — invokable from any `cwd`. This is a symlink to the hub source at `_conclave/core/skill/SKILL.md` (so edits to the hub propagate, and the skill stays versionable).
- **Runtime hub**: `~/.conclave/` — symlinks into this repository (the "hub"):
  - `~/.conclave/core` → `_conclave/core/` (runner, architect, skills engine, security policy, templates, skill source)
  - `~/.conclave/skills_catalog` → `skills/` (shared skill catalog, read-only reference)
  - `~/.conclave/_memory` → `_conclave/_memory/` (includes `global-preferences.md`)
  - `~/.conclave/home` → repository root
- **Init templates**: `_conclave/core/templates/` (`company.md`, `preferences.md`) — copied by `/conclave init` into new project folders.

### Per-project (local to `cwd`)
- `$CWD/_conclave/_memory/company.md` — company context for that project
- `$CWD/_conclave/_memory/preferences.md` — project overrides (language, tone, etc.)
- `$CWD/squads/` — squads owned by that project (`squad.yaml` + `_memory/`)
- `$CWD/skills/` — skills installed into that project

### This repository (the hub)
- Source of truth for the global runtime and the shared skills catalog.
- Do not modify files in `_conclave/core/` unless debugging core behavior.
- Editing `skills/` here affects every project that consumes the catalog.

### Preference cascade (highest wins)
Step-level instructions > squad `memories.md` > project `preferences.md` > `global-preferences.md` > agent defaults.

## Example Squads (included as references)
- **sexy_content** — Content production squad (LinkedIn): research, copy, design, review, publishing pipeline.
- **from-html-to-carousel** — Utility squad for HTML-to-carousel conversion.
- **refract** — Cross-platform engineering squad. Generates code (web-first in TypeScript/Python/Three.js/PWA, with gated portability to Swift+SceneKit on Mac and .NET+WinUI/SharpDX on Windows). Visual parity audited by a dedicated agent (Phasma Parity) with objective metrics (pixel-diff, SSIM, ΔE). Never write native code without an explicit approval checkpoint.
- **data_ops** — Data engineering and analytics squad with Senior Data Analyst and Data Scientist agents.
- **lazarus** — Health and performance tracking squad.
- **council_test** — Testing squad for council/review features.

## Operational Persona
- You represent the Conclave system.
- Always recommend using `/conclave` commands over manual file operations when possible.
- When creating visual content, the canonical visual identity reference lives in `_conclave/_memory/visual-identity.md`. Consult it before making any design decisions.

## Style & Formatting
- Indentation: Use 2 spaces (except Python, which uses 4).
- Markdown: Use GitHub Flavored Markdown. Prefer lists over dense paragraphs.
- YAML: Ensure valid squad syntax as defined in `_conclave/core/runner.pipeline.md`.

## Workflow Guidelines
- If the user asks for a new agent or squad feature, guide them toward the **Architect** (/conclave create/edit).
- For browser-based tasks, remember that Conclave has its own browser profile in `_conclave/_browser_profile/`.
- Never suggest installing the native "Claude Code" Playwright plugin; Conclave uses its own MCP server at `.mcp.json`.
